Description: Managerie's anonymized platform specializes in connecting growth-oriented individuals with organizations in need of cultural champions.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: We started Managerie to give people the space to articulate how they're trying to drive their career, and encourage companies to engage in that narrative. That's why at Managerie we prefer to highlight people's growth orientation, motivators, and best suited work environments, in addition to skills / qualifications and in return, companies are getting a full and honest picture of the human being they'd potentially be hiring. Our currency at Managerie is authenticity. We've designed a process that gets to the core of people's personal drivers and ambitions for their career by making intentional space for a genuine conversation with every candidate. Our primary aim is to get an honest and authentic picture of our candidates and what they need to perform at their best. Managerie is a resource for candidates to help tell their story, and the more real we can be, the more powerful that story becomes. We're excited to be able to offer free access to our anonymous candidate database to any company looking to hire growth-oriented individuals and will only charge a fee when someone is hired. Managerie is committed to creating equal opportunities for people from all races, ethnicities, genders, sexual orientations, religions, and backgrounds, and intentionally exclude human names and brand names from our profiles to minimize biases.

Description: Liifsport is a dynamic crowdfunding platform focusing on niche market segments.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Minneapolis-Saint Paul Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Liifsport is the world’s first and only crowdfunding platform centered around sports innovation and ideas to help revolutionize the sports and recreation industry.  This is accomplished by brokering a relationship between innovators, entrepreneurs and like-minded investors for the advancement of sports around the world. LiifGroup, LLC is the first crowdfunding platform created in Minnesota.  LiifGroup believes crowdfunding is best done when it matches innovative projects tailored toward diverse marketplaces.     Liifsport focuses on projects that will connect the world’s sporting community.  Liifsport offers a unique opportunity to launch a product or service in all areas of the sports marketplace.  Minnesota is a melting pot for sports organizations and businesses.  “Everyone is affected directly or indirectly by sports, whether it’s your kids, your business, your community or maybe you’re just a sports enthusiast.  Being in the center of Minnesota will allow us to provide options for new sports technologies and products to find sufficient funding,” Erik Westrum, Co-Founder and professional hockey player.   LiifGroup, LLC is nearing completion on additional sites geared to startup businesses and charities.  LiifGroup’s goal is to spur innovation for small companies maximizing the power of the crowd utilizing our “Liifcycle” concept of idea + innovation + investing = results.  LiifGroup’s objective is to bring a simple idea to a successful reality through each of its niche market segments.  Unlike crowdfunding predecessor Kickstarter, LiifGroup’s philosophy offers innovators the option to capture any funding reached during their project.  Many crowdfunding sites offer an all-or-none format.  LiifGroup is unique in allowing innovators the option to utilize rewards and equity as part of their funding campaign. According to Forbes, the crowdfunding industry will grow from $1.5 billion in 2011 to $2.8 billion in 2012.  LiifGroup management anticipates continued growth in the area of crowdfunding and crowdsourcing as the new regulations pertaining to the JOBS Act are released later in 2013. Headquartered in Savage, LiifGroup, LLC is one of the leading newcomers in crowdfunding.

Full Description: Radial Function is a collection of senior executives from various sections of the media and gaming industries. Our expertise is in bridging the gap between traditional media properties and the multi-billion dollar gaming space, with particular emphasis on the recent boom in social and casual games and applications.  We have the ability to develop, monetize and distribute on multiple platforms and via multiple distribution fronts such as online, mobile, I-phone, etc.  Our company is currently focused on the 4D's: Design, Develop, Distribute, and Deliver as a mantra and our three key avenues of business are as follows:   1.  Software and Game Development:  We have been engaged and partnered with high profile media and brand properties to develop multi-platform gaming initiatives.  Our proprietary relationships, industry know-how and ability to tap into foreign resources allow us to develop branded games at a fraction of the cost of our competitors.  We are currently out-pacing our competition by over 70% cost savings, and we often take co-development positions putting equity into projects that make sense, and further drive down the cost to our partners.  On key targeted projects we prepare an in depth financial analysis based on aggregate industry data that often leads to development and operations cost resulting in less than 5%-10% of the overall ROI.    2.  Social Media, Gaming and Digital Distribution Transaction and Advisory Practice: As industry leading experts in the field we are often approached to advise on strategic development and transactions in the social media, distribution and gaming spaces.  Our team has the ability to handle all aspects of due diligence and strategic planning, as well as provide EIR services (Entrepreneur in Residence Services) to handle and facilitate internal operations and sales functions for key clients.  We are building a digital consulting practice that acts as a revenue generating center for key partners.    3.  Monetization of Gaming platforms for Advertisers and Brands:  Via extensive game developer relationships we have access to over 35 million monthly active users online, and our proprietary matching software and algorithms enable us to easily integrate brands and advertisers inside of today's casual and social games.  We handle all facets of the media buy and planning and offer full service integration and in certain cases monetization (via sales of virtual goods) of marketing and revenue campaigns.
